# Skill: Source Ingestion

## Purpose

Convert discovered sources into structured records that can be analyzed consistently across the project.

This skill takes entries from the **source registry** and normalizes them into a consistent metadata format.

---

## When to Use

Use this skill after new sources have been discovered and need to be prepared for analysis.

Typical triggers include:

- a new source registry entry
- newly discovered research articles
- newly discovered blog posts or benchmark reports

---

## Inputs

- source registry entries
- source URLs
- discovered source metadata

Example inputs:

- title
- url
- source type
- publication date

---

## Process

1. Access the source URL.
2. Extract key metadata from the source.
3. Normalize the metadata into a consistent format.
4. Capture a short summary describing the source.
5. Prepare the record for later analysis tasks.

---

## Output Format

Each ingested source should produce a structured record containing:

- title
- author (if available)
- date
- url
- source_type
- summary

Example output:

title: SAP’s ABAP-1 Loses Every ABAP Benchmark  
author: Marian Zeis  
date: 2025-XX-XX  
url: https://example.com/article  
source_type: blog  
summary: Article discussing benchmark results comparing ABAP agents with other language ecosystems.

---

## Notes

This skill focuses on **metadata normalization and preparation**, not deep interpretation of the content.

Detailed analysis is performed by the **literature_analysis** skill.